<FIRST>r a AM-LynnFire     08-16 0169</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Lynn Fire,0173</SECOND>
<HEAD>Investigators Uncover Fourth Body from Amid Charred Rooming House
Rubble</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LYNN, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Investigators uncovered a fourth body Tuesday
from the rubble at a charred rooming house, the site of a fatal fire
officials believe was triggered by an arsonist.
   Stephen F. O'Connell, a spokesman for Essex County District
Attorney Kevin Burke, said authorities located the body on the Ben
Crest Plaza's top floor about 3:30 p.m.
   ``What happened is in the course of re-interviewing witnesses the
detectives determined they should go back to the building and search
a particular area. On doing so, the body was found,'' O'Connell said.
   The victim was not immediately identified, but forensics experts
were were being consulted, O'Connell said.
   He said so far no suspects had been linked with the fire, which
burned out of control for three hours a week ago and killed at least
three other people. Authorities said the building had several safety
violations.
   Investigators were still tracking down leads in the case,
O'Connell said.
</TEXT>
