<HEAD>German Fails in Border Escape Attempt When Vehicle Flips Over</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERLIN (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An East German failed in an attempt to escape to
West Berlin when the truck he was driving flipped over after
striking a border barrier, police said today.
   West Berlin police said Communist East German border guards
quickly surrounded the man and dragged him from the vehicle shortly
before midnight Tuesday at the Stolpe crossing point between East
Germany and West Berlin.
