<HEAD>President to Give First TV Speech Sept. 5 on Drug Plan</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Bush-Drugs Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush will discuss his new drug policy in a
televised speech to the nation on Sept. 5, White House spokesman
Marlin Fitzwater said today.
   Bush is to unveil the details of his administration's war on
drugs, which reportedly will cost $7.5 billion, earlier that day.
   Fitzwater, speaking with reporters aboard Air Force One en route
to Miami, said Bush felt the issue was important enough to warrant a
nationwide TV address, which will be the first of his presidency.
   The spokesman said the address probably would come from the White
House, although the exact location and time have not been determined.
</TEXT>
