<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--China-Drought     08-16 0142</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--China-Drought,0146</SECOND>
<HEAD>Drought Hits Wide Areas of China</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Drought has struck wide areas of China _ from
southwestern Sichuan province to the northern cities of Beijing and
Tianjin _ endangering crops and supplies of drinking water, official
reports said Wednesday.
   The droughts in northern China, stretching as far west as
Xinjiang province, have parched 27.84 million acres of land and
affected water supplies for more than 6 million people, the People's
Daily newspaper said.
   Millions of workers have been recruited to help save crops in
those regions affected by lower-than-average rainfall, it said.
   In northeasternmost Heilongjiang province, more than 40 percent
of the province's grain and soybean crops, about 5.75 million acres,
have been affected, the Xinhua News Agency said.
   Average rainfall for parts of the province in August has been
about 80 percent below normal, it said.
