<HEAD>Man Accused of Carrying Crack Cocaine in Women's Undergarments</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GREENWICH, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man was arrested on drug charges after
police found more than 125 vials of crack stuffed into the bra and
panties he was wearing, police said.
   Curtis Rock, 34, of Stamford was arrested Monday after police,
acting on an anonymous tip, stopped a car in which he was a
passenger, Deputy Police Chief Kenneth Moughty said.
   During a search of the vehicle, police found 41 empty crack
vials, Moughty said. The other vials were discoverd during a strip
search at police headquarters, Moughty said.
   He was charged with possession of narcotics, possession of
narcotics with intent to sell, destruction of evidence and
possession of drug paraphernalia, Moughty said.
   The car's driver, Darryl Mayer, 47, of Stamford, was charged with
possession of drug paraphernalia, Moughty said. He was also charged
with driving without a license and given a written warning for
failure to drive right.
   Both men are due in court Aug. 23.
</TEXT>
