<TEXT>
   A special runoff election to fill the unexpired
term of former House Speaker Jim Wright will be held Tuesday, Sept.
12, Gov. Bill Clements said Wednesday.
   In the special election Saturday for the 12th congressional
district, Republican Dr. Bob Lanier collected 21,978, or 39.39
percent of the vote, and Democrat Pete Geren, won 17,751, or 31.81
percent in the eight-candidate race.
   A runoff between the top two vote getters is required because no
candidate in the special election received a majority of votes cast.
   Wright, a Democrat who resigned amid numerous allegations of
ethics violations, received 53 write-in votes.
