<SECOND>BC-British Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru,0139</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Stocks End Sharply Higher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prices rallied strongly on London's Stock Exchange
Wednesday, boosted by a reluctance to sell stock, renewed
speculative interest and an upward move on Wall Street.
   But dealers said there was little institutional buying interest,
as many players remained on the sidelines ahead of U.S. and British
economic data to be released Thursday and Friday.
   ``Buying interest was fairly average but the market rose because
there was almost no selling pressure whatsoever,'' one dealer said.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index closed at a
session high of 2,345.8, up 19.6 points, or 0.8 percent.
   Volume came to 449.8 million shares, up from 436.7 million shares
Tuesday.
   At the London close, the Dow Jones industrial average was up 6.64
points at 2,694.42.
