<SECOND>BC-Wang,0142</SECOND>
<HEAD>Wang Says Negotiations Continuing On Debt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOWELL, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Wang Laboratories Inc. will not make certain
principal and interest payments on its institutional debt while
negotiations with its bank lenders continue, company Chairman An
Wang said in a statement issued Wednesday.
   Wang did not provide any further details about the step and
neither he nor company spokesmen could be reached immediately for
comment.
   Wang has been negotiating a restructuring of its debt with its
lenders.
   The computer company recently reported a $424.3 million loss for
the fiscal year that ended June 30 and has been attempting to reach
an agreement to restructure a total of $962 million in short- and
long-term debt.
   Last week, the company and the banks extended existing loans to
Wednesday after failing to reach a restructuring agreement.
