<HEAD>Field's Says Ohio Store Mirrors Chicago Revamp</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOHN CHALFANT</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Marshall Field's adds Ohio to the short
list of states in which it operates with the opening this week of a
$25 million store that Chairman Philip B. Miller said mirrors
renovation underway at Field's flagship outlet.
   Miller said Hambrecht, Terrell International, the New York
architectural firm that designed the Columbus store, also has been
working on a renovation of 1 million square feet at Field's landmark
store in Chicago.
