of retailing. And a lot of elements that you will see in this (Ohio)
building ... recall the significant, historic architectural features
of our State Street store (in Chicago),'' Miller said Wednesday.
   The $110 million Chicago project is to be completed in 1992.
   Field's, which operates 15 stores in Illinois, four in Wisconsin,
and four in Texas, opens its first store in Ohio on Friday, a
200,000-square-foot anchor of a $200 million shopping mall built to
revitalize a section of the capital city's downtown.
   An open atrium is the focal point of the three-level Field's
store, which includes a replica of the unique clock that is a
landmark at the State Street store.
   It is the first new department store in almost three years for
Field's, a division of BAT Industries PLC, a British
tobacco-insurance-retailing conglomerate. The last one opened in San
Antonio, Texas, in October 1986.
